    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-29T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-29T08:00:00-05:00" n="453"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2877: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Vigo</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stewart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vigo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-29T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >August 29, 1936—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Rebel army claims slow progress on all fronts and that communications are
                    restored to Navarre to east, Seville and Cadiz to southward, Castropol and Tineo
                    in Asturias. Also state that daily trains now running from Seville to Alsasua,
                    Navarre. Also claim three-fourths national territory and two-thirds population
                    already dominated. Twelve Italian aviators with airplanes arrived here yesterday
                    and forwarded to Burgos. Reliably informed two German vessels heavily loaded
                    with “pineapples and grapes” arrived here yesterday morning. Vigo and Galicia as
                    a whole remain tranquil although military are condemning and killing daily
                    numbers of Madrid Government agents. Fascist militia running rampant in outlying
                    districts and summarily executing suspected Communists.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stewart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
